body.description: Band-Aid Brand Tru-Stay Sheer Strips Adhesive Bandages offer comfortable, sheer protection of minor cuts and scrapes. These Band-Aid Brand Adhesive Bandages provide lightweight, breathable protection. The Microvent backing of these sheer bandages, along with the air channels on the Quilt-Aid pad, provide superior breathability. These Band-Aid Brand Tru-Stay Sheer Strips Adhesive Bandages are also made with a unique Quilt-Aid Comfort Pad that is designed to cushion painful wounds while you heal. The Hurt-Free pad won't stick to the wound, allowing for gentle removal. This package includes 80 sheer bandages in assorted sizes.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: BAND-AID Brand Adhesive Bandages Comfort Sheer BAND-AID Brand Adhesive Bandages Comfort Sheer are designed to be more flexible than ordinary plastic bandages. This design helps them to stay in place while they cover and protect minor wounds. These bandages feature a Quiltvent Pad with air channels and Microvent backing for superior breathability. The pad wicks away blood to keep the wound clean and is nonstick for comfortable removal. Heals The Hurt Faster A covered wound heals faster than an uncovered one.* BAND-AID Brand Adhesive Bandages have a non-stick Hurt-Free Pad that won't stick to the wound for gentle removal. Clean, Treat, Protect When you or a loved one has a minor injury, you want it to heal as quickly as possible. Minor cuts and scrapes can become contaminated with dirt and germs, which may cause infection and delay healing. That’s why BAND-AID Brand of Adhesive Bandages recommends an easy-to-follow 3-step process. Clean, treat, and protect your wounds to avoid infection and promote healing. At a Glance: With Quiltvent Pad for superior breathability Sheer, flexible design Non-stick Hurt-Free Pad that won't stick to the wound for gentle removal

Step 1: Clean Cleaning a wound is the first step to a quick and proper recovery. To complete this step, clean the affected area using a mild soap and saline water and Neosporin First Aid Antiseptic Foaming Liquid for Kids. Blot dry with a sterile BAND-AID Brand of First Aid Products Mirabsorb Gauze Sponge. Step 2: Treat Once the affected area is cleaned, continue to the second step of the regimen, treatment. Treat the wound with Neosporin + Pain, Itch, Scar ointment to help prevent infection and aid in the relief of pain or discomfort in minor cuts, scrapes, and burns. Step 3: Protect After treating the affected area, protect the wound until it is completely healed with a BAND-AID Brand Adhesive Bandage like a Comfort Sheer Adhesive Bandage.

About BAND-AID Brand Adhesive Bandages BAND-AID Brand Adhesive Bandages have long been a staple in a family’s first-aid kit as a source of comfort and protection. Today BAND-AID Brand Adhesive Bandages are America’s #1 Bandage Brand!** In a world full of cuts, scrapes and blisters it seems hard to imagine life without those little adhesive bandages. BAND-AID Brand Adhesive Bandages has moved from being strictly a bandage to becoming a brand that offers a wide variety of products to meet the diverse needs of today’s active families and their lifestyles. From 1920 to today, we’ve stuck with you through the years and hope our products inspire you to express yourself. Our mission is to cover all your wound-protection needs in a fun and stylish way.

*BAND-AID Brand Adhesive Bandages Sheer Bandages, data on file. **200 moms with children ages 3-11 were surveyed via Toluna’s national consumer panel. Each panelist was screened for age, gender, presence of children, and age of children before being asked about category and product recommendation. Differences between response groups were verified using a Z-test of proportions, applying a 95% confidence level as the minimum threshold for claim validation. 64% of 314 survey respondents qualified as category recommenders, the overwhelming majority of whom selected BAND-AID Brand Adhesive Bandages as the brand they recommend most. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love it. Very BIG
reviews.reviewText: I purchased these big bandages for my 2 yr. Old. She needed bandages quick and these were eligible for instant delivery. They stick very well. She was even trying to peel it off and it wouldn’t come off.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Band-Aid Brand is considered the best for reasons...
reviews.reviewText: Band-Aid Brand is better than other brands in several ways. One of the most important is the way the Band-Aid brand stays on your skin for a lot longer than other brands I have tried. Another great point is the protective material that you put over your sore is very soft, and I believe is thicker than other brands. Also, when it is time to remove the Band-Aid, it comes off without ripping your skin! Go for the little more expensive brand and you will get a much better band-aid.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars They stay on!
reviews.reviewText: I have tried a lot of off brands, they don’t stay on for long. I went back to these and don’t have to change them during the day. They stay on!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Not great for the hands
reviews.reviewText: I’ve been trying to find a band aid that will work on the back of my hands for a couple super small areas. These are a great size, but they tend to fall off after a few hours because of all the movement.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for smaller use
reviews.reviewText: I purchased these to use on smaller area such as on my face or arms or on toes for some protection of smaller injuries. They work perfectly for me. They stick well and can be a bit more difficult to get off due to the excellence in adhesion, but I would rather have that than something that won't stick. I like that they are clear so you can see them very well. Now, if they just came in a larger than 50 pack.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Love these. I don’t heal well, so I need to cover up every little spot, these are perfect size. They even stay on in the shower. Hard to find. So happy to get these.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars I really liked the Sheer Strip Band-aids and these aren't as good
reviews.reviewText: I used Sheer Strip Band-aids for decades and now they aren't available and I really don't like these very much at all. The Sheer Strip pad went from edge to edge of the adhesive part and I liked that much better as the edges just sit there and dangle out and don't stick and then water gets in anyway so it isn't water resistant in the least. I am a pharmacist and the harsh soaps that are used in hospitals cause my cuticles near the end of my nails to split and they bleed and are very painful. I have always put antibiotic ointment and a a band-aid to cover them and to get them to heal. The newer versions are not nearly as good and I have been doing this for 40 years. So this is not a new thing with me. Thank you Corporate America for fixing things that aren't broken. Oh and the newest ones don't have a flange of folded over paper so that when you pull off the second part of the paper just before placing it, it is unavoidable to contaminate the pad with one's finger and the whole point of having that part be sterile is so that your wound doesn't get bacteria in there. Even better!!!
